Cell.Text: [S] G|And I won't miss you.
[S] G|Finally! I thought it would never happen.

Node.Caption: 0_knm_mour_dialogue_dismissTopic: It's time for us to part ways. I'm tired of you.

Cell.Text: So you need something or not?
Stop wasting my time.
Think faster.
[S] G|What, too helpless to do it yourself?
[S] G|Well, what is it this time?
[S] G|This is the last time, okay?
[S] G|You're in time. I was just about to leave.
[S] G|I won't wait long. I'll go away when I want.
[S] Poor little Dragonborn, too weak to carry your own.
[S] If this isn't a new armor for me, I'm selling your junk.
[S] Do you always carry so much useless junk?
[S] Why should I carry it?
G|I think you'll like my sword in your throat.
G|I think I was in a coma. Or I died. I don't know. But when I woke up, I saw Alduin. He didn't speak with me, just looked. | When he flew away, I didn't know what to do.

Node.Caption: 0_knm_mour_dialogue_wherehap: Where have you been all this time?

Cell.Text: The world has changed a lot. I think more than a century may have passed.
I.. I don't know. The last thing I remember - I was badly wounded.
G|Maybe next time.
G|Long ago, I had all that I wanted. But time takes it away from me.
G|All my family died many centuries ago. I don't know the fate of my race. Perhaps I am the last.
G|I don't think we need to talk about such sad things. Better - let's go kill somebody!
G|As long as you are weak - you don't deserve any other treatment, mortal creature.
G|If you really think that everyone should love you just for being a Dohvahkiin, you are seriously wrong.
Choose your words carefully.
I'm listening.
Make it quick.

Node.Caption: 0_knm_mour_dialogue_iwanttotalk: I want to say something to you.
